reviews.review_text: LISTEN  Nice matrix blend. Inspired performance. Some surprises if you don’t scan the set list first. 1985, Twenty Years So Far.

I've got no idea Mom After about 3 years of going to shows my mom got curious enough that she said yes to an invite.  Not as close as the Greek or BCT but an easy drive.  We sat in the balcony to the side of the stage, great closeup view of the band.  When the show started and the audience went nuts mom turned to me and asked "what is this, why is the audience so excited?" I had to explain, "I've got no idea mom, I've never heard this before."  It wouldn't be the only time that night.

The 2nd set was all that I love in a show, mixing and matching, going where the energy took them.  One of my favorite memories was watching Bob, as Gimme Some Lovin' was nearing it's end, walk around the stage telling the band "Midnight Hour" (we had the angle and were close enough that I swear I read his lips).  

Then that encore - "I've got no idea, mom."
